<HEADLINE> Easton Gets AP Post in Lubbock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LUBBOCK, Texas (AP) -- Pam Easton, a newswoman in the Atlanta  
bureau of The Associated Press, has been named the news 
cooperative's correspondent in Lubbock. 
</P>
<P>
	The appointment was announced Friday by Texas Chief of Bureau  
John Lumpkin. 
</P>
<P>
	Easton began her AP career as a part-time editorial assistant in  
the Dallas bureau while a student at Southern Methodist University. 
She joined the cooperative full-time upon graduation and became a 
newswoman in 1997. She transferred to Atlanta the following year. 
</P>
<P>
	Easton, 25, succeeds Chris Newton, who is transferring to AP's  
bureau in Harrisburg, Pa. 
  	   	
