<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Push Upward; Dow Up 101.95 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks moved sharply higher in early trading  
today, extending yesterday's late rebound from a steep selloff 
sparked by a profit warning from IBM. 
</P>
<P>
	In the first hour of trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones  
industrial average was up 101.95 at 10,399.64, wiping out 
Thursday's 94-point decline. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were also posting sizable gains. The  
Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 11.84 at 1,295.45, and the 
Nasdaq composite index was up 36.71 at 2,838.66. 
</P>
<P>
	With no major economic reports to steer the market, investors  
were focusing on the continuing flood of company reports on the 
just-ended third-quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	Shares of Gillette slid $3.68 3/4 to $34.18 3/4 after the consumer  
products maker's report late Thursday met most profit forecasts but 
warned that fourth-quarter sales and earnings are likely to decline 
because of inventory problems. 
</P>
<P>
	On Thursday, the Dow closed with a loss of 94.67 after  
recovering from a 213-point slide. The broad market also rallied 
late in the day, with the technology-dominated Nasdaq composite 
turning higher despite the discouraging news from IBM. 
</P>
<P>
	Late Wednesday, IBM warned that customers are postponing  
purchases of network and database machines, fearful of that complex 
system upgrades will make them more vulnerable to the Year 2000 
computer bug. 
</P>
<P>
	Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 2-to-1 ratio on the  
New York Stock Exchange and a slightly smaller margin on the Nasdaq 
Stock Market. 
</P>
<P>
	NYSE volume totaled 126.54 million shares, almost even with  
Thursday's early pace. 
</P>
<P>
	The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies was up 2.76 at  
417.03. 
</P>
<P>
	Overseas, Japan's Nikkei stock average slipped 0.05 percent. In  
afternoon trading, Germany's DAX index was up 1.83 percent, 
Britain's FT-SE 100 was up 1.40 percent, and France's CAC-40 was up 
1.57 percent. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
