<HEADLINE> Amtrak Train Derails, 3 Injuries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CATHEDRAL CITY, Calif. (AP) -- Nine cars of Amtrak's Sunset  
Limited derailed early Friday, shutting down a major rail line in 
the desert east of Los Angeles but causing no serious injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	There were three minor injuries, said Ray Dampier of the  
Riverside County Fire Department. Amtrak spokesman Cliff Black said 
the injuries were minor bumps. The westbound train from Orlando, 
Fla., to Los Angeles was carrying 216 passengers and 18 crew 
members. 
</P>
<P>
	Three of the Sunset Limited's passenger cars, a private  
passenger car and five freight cars jumped the track near 
Interstate 10 in the northeast area of the city, said Mark Davis of 
Union Pacific, which operates the track. 
</P>
<P>
	The cars remained upright. Passengers were taken by bus to Los  
Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	The site is just east of Palm Springs and about 110 miles east  
of Los Angeles. The rail line was expected to reopen late Friday. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
