<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fla. Crash Kills 2 British Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DAVENPORT, Fla. (AP) -- A dump truck ran a red light and collided  
with a rental van carrying six English tourists to the airport for 
their flight home. Two of the tourists were killed, including a 
pregnant woman, and two were critically injured. 
</P>
<P>
	The crash happened Thursday at a highway intersection in  
Davenport, 30 miles southwest of Orlando. Witnesses said the 
tourists had been on vacation at Disney World and were en route to 
the airport to return to England. 
</P>
<P>
	The van was rented to Martin Griffith of Petersham, England.  
With him were his pregnant wife, Carolyn Griffith; their children, 
9-year-old Jordan and 7-year-old Megan; and Ronald and Linda New of 
Bedfont, England. 
</P>
<P>
	The truck driver, Daniel Adams II, apparently ran a red light,  
the Florida Highway Patrol said. Charges were pending. He was 
unhurt. 
</P>
<P>
	New and Ms. Griffith died instantly. Ms. New, 53, was in  
critical but stable condition, and Griffith was in stable condition 
today, said Bill West, a supervisor at Lakeland Regional Medical 
Center. Megan was in critical condition and Jordan was in stable 
condition at Arnold Palmer Hospital for Children and Women. 
</P>
<P>
	All of the occupants in the van were wearing seat belts, Trooper  
D.W. Taylor said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
