<HEADLINE> WNBA Expansion Teams To Join League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- WNBA expansion teams in Indianapolis, Miami,  
Portland and Seattle have met the requirements for season-ticket 
sales and will join the league as planned in 2000. 
</P>
<P>
	Indiana and Miami will be added to the Eastern Conference,  
joining Charlotte, Cleveland, Detroit, New York, Orlando and 
Washington. 
</P>
<P>
	Portland and Seattle will play in the Western Conference with  
Houston, Los Angeles, Minnesota, Phoenix, Sacramento and Utah. 
</P>
<P>
	The league chose the new teams in early June and gave them until  
Oct. 15 to secure pledges for at least 5,500 season tickets. Each 
team topped the requirement and met other conditions set by the 
league. 
</P>
<P>
	The announcement by the league Friday was considered a  
formality, as the new teams have already made several personnel and 
organizational moves. 
</P>
<P>
	``The fan support demonstrated in each of these cities has been  
truly outstanding,'' WNBA president Val Ackerman said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
