<HEADLINE> MediaOne Shareowners OK AT&AMP;T Merger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ENGLEWOOD, Colo. (AP) -- MediaOne Group shareowners have approved  
the proposed merger with AT&AMP;T. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is a key milestone in the process,'' said Chuck Lillis,  
chairman of MediaOne Group. He said the company hopes to close the 
merger early next year. 
</P>
<P>
	C. Michael Armstrong, AT&AMP;T chairman, said the merger is a vote  
of confidence in the company's strategy to provide millions of 
families with a choice in local phone service. 
</P>
<P>
	He said after the company gets regulatory approval, the merged  
company can move forward in broadband video, voice and data 
services to more communities. 
</P>
<P>
	MediaOne Group is one of the world's largest broadband  
communications companies. The company also has investments in 
foreign wireless communications. 
</P>
<P>
	About 99 percent of the shareholders who voted on Thursday  
approved the merger. 




  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
