<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gove, Heintz Tied in Nike Tour  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DOTHAN, Ala. (AP) -- Jeff Gove and Bob Heintz remained tied for  
the lead at 8-under 136 on Friday after two rounds of the Nike Tour 
Championship at Highland Oaks Golf Course. 
</P>
<P>
	Edward Fryatt was third after a 69, three strokes back, while  
Marco Dawson had a 68 and was at 140. Brian Tennyson (68), Jim M. 
Johnson (70) and Marco Gortana (72) were another stroke back. 
</P>
<P>
	The identical 68s by Gove and Heintz in the first two rounds  
marked the first time in the championship's history that the same 
co-leaders have led more than one round together. 
</P>
<P>
	Casey Martin, fighting for his PGA Tour card, had a 71 Friday  
and was eight strokes off the pace at 144, tied for 16th with five 
others. Martin entered the $400,000 event, the last on the Nike 
Tour this season, 12th on the money list. 
</P>
<P>
	The top 15 finishers on the money list earn their exempt status  
to play on the PGA Tour next year. 
</P>
<P>
	Leading money-winner Carl Paulson had a 75 Friday and was at  
147. The low round Friday was by Curt Byrum, who shot a 67 and made 
the biggest move of the round, from 41st to 10th at 143. 
</P>
<P>
	Heintz is No. 16 on the money list, just $141 behind No. 15 Dick  
Mast, who shot 75s in the first two rounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Gove, who ranks 20th on the money list at $99,692, failed to  
record a birdie on his first 27 holes at last year's Nike Tour 
Championship, but in the first two rounds this year has 12 to lead 
the field. Heintz was next with 11, and Fryatt had 10. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
