<HEADLINE> House Voucher Roll Call </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The 257-166 roll call Thursday by which the House rejected an  
amendment to the Title I bill that would have given poor children 
in low-performing or dangerous schools $3,500 to transfer to a 
better public, private or parochial school. 
</P>
<P>
	A ``yes'' vote is a vote to approve the measure.  
</P>
<P>
	Voting yes were 3 Democrats and 163 Republicans.  
</P>
<P>
	Voting no were 204 Democrats, 52 Republicans and 1 Independent.  
</P>
<P>
	X denotes those not voting.  
</P>
<P>
	There is one vacancy in the 435-member House.  


