<HEADLINE> Dolphins' Marino Still Ailing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DAVIE, Fla. (AP) -- Ailing Dan Marino did not throw in practice  
for the third day in a row Friday, and he'll likely miss his first 
start since 1996 when the Miami Dolphins play the Philadelphia 
Eagles on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Dan did take a few snaps and did some conditioning work,''  
coach Jimmy Johnson said. ``We'll make a decision Sunday morning as 
far as what his contribution will be.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Marino has thrown on the sideline this week, but he can't  
generate much velocity or distance because of muscle weakness 
caused by a bone spur in his lower neck. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson said earlier this week that he expected Damon Huard to  
make his first NFL start in place of Marino. Huard came off the 
bench in the first quarter last Sunday and rallied Miami past New 
England 31-30. 
</P>
<P>
	Huard worked with the first team again Friday.  
</P>
<P>
	``I liked what I saw,'' Johnson said.  
  	   	
</P>
