<HEADLINE> Georgetown 14, St. Peter's 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JERSEY CITY, N.J. (AP) -- Aaron Brown and Rob Belli each ran for  
touchdowns, leading Georgetown to a 14-3 victory over St. Peter's 
on Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Georgetown (6-1) returned to the win column after losing for the  
first time in a non-league game last Saturday against Davidson. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown opened the scoring on a four-yard touchdown run with 8:18  
left in the first quarter. Belli scored from a yard out with 8:53 
left in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	St. Peter's (1-6), which lost its fifth straight game, got its  
only score on a 28-yard field goal by David Wiggan. The field goal 
was Wiggan's fifth of the season, tying the school record set by 
Anthony Guma in 1993. 
  	   	
