<HEADLINE> London Shares Close Higher / British Stocks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- Share prices rose sharply Friday on the London  
Stock Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	The Financial Times Stock Exchange 100-Share index closed up  
119.6 points, or 2.0 percent, at 6,058.9. 
</P>
<P>
	Provisional volume in London was 1.1 billion shares traded  
compared with 1.25 billion on Thursday . 
</P>
<P>
	Technology shares recovered Friday from the previous day's big  
losses. 
</P>
<P>
	But fears of a massive Florida lawsuit pay-out for the cigarette  
industry continued to damage tobacco stocks. British American 
Tobacco shares led the FTSE 100 decliners, losing 8.8 percent 
following Thursday's 12 percent slide. 
</P>
<P>
	Shares in the Reuters media and information group fell 4.9  
percent on top of a 13 percent fall Thursday after the media and 
financial information company reported flat sales. 
</P>
<P>
	Telecommunications shares were mixed.  



  	   	
</P>
