<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Stock Market, 
and American Stock Exchange. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	
</P>
<P>
	Gillette, down 1 3/4 at 36 1/8  
</P>
<P>
	The consumer product maker's fourth-quarter sales and earnings  
are likely to decline because of inventory problems, casting a pall 
on a third-quarter report that met analyst expectations. 

</P>
<P>
	American Express, up 3 3/4 at 148 5/8  
</P>
<P>
	J.P. Morgan, up 7 5/8 at 124 13/16  
</P>
<P>
	Citigroup, up 1 1/4 at 48 3/16  
</P>
<P>
	Allstate, up 13/16 at 25  
</P>
<P>
	Republicans and Democrats resolved a dispute on bank lending  
rules that threatened to derail a major overhaul of the financial 
services laws. The proposed bill would lift Depression-era legal 
barriers and allow banks, brokerage firms and insurance companies 
to merge and sell each other's products. 

</P>
<P>
	Student Loan Corp., up 7 1/8 at 47 9/16  
</P>
<P>
	Citigroup offered to pay $45 a share in cash for the remaining  
20 percent of the student lender, which is based in Stamford, Conn. 
Also late Thursday, Student Loan reported 22 percent increase in 
third-quarter earnings to $19.6 million. 

</P>
<P>
	AmeriSource Health, down 4 7/16 at 12 3/16  
</P>
<P>
	The health maintenance organization warned that it will post  
weak results for its fourth quarter ended Sept. 30. AmeriSource, 
based in Malvern, Pa., said revenue was less than expected due to 
delays in new business. 

</P>
<P>
	Pillowtex, down 3/8 at 5 3/8  
</P>
<P>
	The Dallas-based maker of home furnishings warned that it will  
post an unexpected loss for the third quarter and a disappointing 
profit for the current quarter. Pillowtex cited 
higher-than-expected marketing expenses and costs for idling of 
machinery. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	
</P>
<P>
	Biogen, down 8 3/16 at 64 3/8  
</P>
<P>
	The drugmaker halted several patient trials of Antova after  
problems involving blood clots arose. Biogen has been developing 
Antova to treat autoimmune diseases such as multiple sclerosis and 
lupus, and for organ transplantation. Biogen is based in Cambridge, 
Mass. 

</P>
<P>
	Ericsson, up 5 1/4 at 39 1/16  
</P>
<P>
	The Swedish maker of mobile phones and telecommunications  
equipment posted better than expected profits. Ericsson also it may 
post sales growth of up to 15 percent for the year, exceeding 
previous expectations. 

</P>
<P>
	Inktomi, down 17 7/16 at 103 1/16  
</P>
<P>
	Merrill Lynch downgraded the Internet software maker despite a  
better-than-expected profit report. Merrill analyst Henry Blodget 
cited a high stock price and a higher estimate of Inktomi's 
operating loss for the company's just-started fiscal year. Inktomi 
is based in Foster City, Calif. 

</P>
<P>
	Viant, up 18 3/4 at 89 1/4  
</P>
<P>
	The Internet commerce consulting firm posted an unexpected  
third-quarter profit as revenues surged 254 percent from year-ago 
levels. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
