<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Two British Tourists Killed in Fla. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DAVENPORT, Fla. (AP) -- A dump truck allegedly ran a red light  
and collided with a rental van carrying six English tourists to the 
airport for their flight home, the Florida Highway Patrol and 
witnesses said. Two of the tourists were killed, including a 
pregnant woman. 
</P>
<P>
	The crash happened Thursday at a highway intersection in  
Davenport, 30 miles southwest of Orlando. According to witnesses, 
the tourists had been on vacation at Disney World and were en route 
to the airport to return to England. 
</P>
<P>
	The van was rented to Martin Griffith of Petersen, England. In  
the vehicle with him were Carolyn Griffith, Ronald New, Linda New, 
53, Jordan Griffith, 9, and Megan Griffith, 7. Authorities said 
Ronald New and Carolyn Griffith died instantly. 
</P>
<P>
	All of the occupants in the van were wearing seat belts, FHP  
investigating officer Trooper D.W. Taylor said. Their relationships 
were not immediately disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
	The patrol said the truck driver, Daniel Adams II, apparently  
ran a red light. Charges were pending. 
</P>
<P>
	Griffith was listed in stable condition today, while Linda New  
was in critical but stable condition, said Bill West, a supervisor 
at Lakeland Regional Medical Center. The extent of New's injuries 
was not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
	Jordan was being treated for chest and abdominal injuries and  
was in stable condition at Arnold Palmer Hospital for Children and 
Women. Megan Griffith was in critical condition, breathing with the 
help of a respirator. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
