<HEADLINE> Report: Disney, Hong Kong Agree </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HONG KONG (AP) -- Walt Disney Co. and the Hong Kong government  
have reportedly reached key agreements on how to finance a new 
theme park here, as the two sides finalize details ahead of the 
Oct. 31 deadline. 
</P>
<P>
	The government will provide the roads and other related  
infrastructure, but Disney must give the city some kind of 
financial compensation for the land, the independent Sing Tao Daily 
reported, quoting unidentified government sources. 
</P>
<P>
	Hong Kong has been in negotiations with the Burbank,  
Calif.-based Disney for months, but had to extend the talks over 
the summer, saying at the time that financial obstacles remained. 
</P>
<P>
	Peggy Chau, a government spokeswoman, refused to comment on the  
report, but said an announcement is expected by Oct. 31. 
</P>
<P>
	Financial Secretary Donald Tsang reportedly said this week the  
government is ready to talk to rival Universal Studios if it cannot 
reach a deal with Disney by the end of the month. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
