<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Woodhall To Defend WBC Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TELFORD, England (AP) -- Richie Woodhall, hoping to unify the  
world super-middleweight title, defends his WBC title Saturday 
night against Germany's Markus Beyer. 
</P>
<P>
	Woodhall, fighting in his home town at the Telford Ice Rink, is  
making the third defense of the title he won in March 1998 from 
South Africa's Sugar Boy Malinga. 
</P>
<P>
	Woodhall won a disputed decision six months later over Glenn  
Catley, then stopped Italy's Vincenzo Nardiello in six rounds last 
February. 
</P>
<P>
	Woodhall has a 25-1 record, his only defeat coming in a  
final-round knockout by American Keith Holmes for the WBC 
middleweight title in 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	Woodhall is hoping to follow up a victory over Beyer with  
unification showdowns against WBO champion Joe Calzaghe of Britain 
and IBF champion Sven Ottke of Germany. 
</P>
<P>
	``I want to unify the super-middleweight division by this time  
next year,'' Woodhall said. 
</P>
<P>
	But Beyer, unbeaten in 16 fights, has plans of his own.  
</P>
<P>
	``Woodhall is ready to be beaten,'' he said. ``I have watched  
his last two fights on tape and nothing he did remotely impressed 
me.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
