<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-22 13:00:21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Penn St. To Go After Star QB Brees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WEST LAFAYETTE, Ind. (AP) -- Penn State long has been known as  
Linebacker University. Nine former linebackers have earned 
All-America honors in the 34 years Joe Paterno has been coach. 
</P>
<P>
	This year's trio of LaVar Arrington, Brandon Short and Mac  
Morrison possibly could join the list of linebackers who went on to 
successful NFL careers -- Jack Ham, John Skorupan, Ed O'Neil, Greg 
Buttle, Kurt Allerman, Shane Conlan and Andre Collins. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think it's safe to say that they have the three best  
linebackers in the conference, certainly as a group,'' Purdue coach 
Joe Tiller said. 
</P>
<P>
	Short leads the team with 50 tackles, including six for losses.  
Arrington has 10 tackles for 40 yards in losses among his 34 
tackles, including three sacks. 
</P>
<P>
	On Saturday, Purdue's record-setting quarterback Drew Brees  
faces the trio as the second-ranked Nittany Lions visit Ross-Ade 
Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
	Penn State (7-0, 3-0 Big Ten) is the conference's only  
undefeated team after No. 16 Purdue (5-2, 2-2) downed previously 
unbeaten Michigan State 52-28 last Saturday. The Boilermakers have 
won 10 straight on their home field where their only loss since 
Tiller took over in 1997 was to Penn State. The Lions, who lead the 
series 4-1-1, won here 42-17 that year and won 31-13 at State 
College last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Brees and Tiller had more concerns than Penn State's linebackers  
while preparing for a fourth consecutive game against a Top 25 
team. Defensive end Courtney Brown is a major reason Penn State's 
front line is considered one the best in college football. Brown 
has only 27 tackles, but 15 were for losses and he leads the 
Nittany Lions with six sacks. 
</P>
<P>
	Arrington and Brown are among 12 semifinalists for the Lombardi  
Award, presented to the nation's top lineman, and Tiller thinks 
they and Short are going to be first-round draft picks. 
</P>
<P>
	Arrington, the first sophomore to be chosen the Big Ten  
defensive player of the year last year when he was a second-team 
All-America, also is a favorite to win the Butkus Award awarded 
annually to the linebacker considered the best in the nation. 
</P>
<P>
	``Arrington is a a threat to make a play -- the play -- at any  
time,'' Tiller said. ``You have to account for him, know where he 
is at all times.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Brees faced Penn State's defense last year. He was sacked only  
16 times last season -- the fewest sacks allowed by any Big Ten 
Conference team. Penn State had six of them. 
</P>
<P>
	``Penn State's front seven is incredible, so we're going to have  
to get the ball off quick,'' Brees said. ``We're going to have to 
execute well. Their secondary, they have good athletes with a lot 
of speed. And they run an all-around good scheme.'' 
</P>
<P>
	This year, Brees has been sacked only five times, while Penn  
State has recorded 23 sacks. 
</P>
<P>
	Tiller contends that Penn State's defense, with nine returnees  
from 1998, is as dominant as last year. Penn State is 19th 
nationally in total defense (299.7 yards per game) and 13th in 
scoring defense (16.0 points per game). 
</P>
<P>
	``It makes for a lot of sleepless nights getting ready for these  
guys,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The game matches the two most productive offenses in the  
conference. Purdue leads the Big Ten in total offense with a 464.6 
average. Penn State is second at 459.3. Penn State leads the 
conference with a 36.7 scoring average, followed by Purdue at 35.7. 
</P>
<P>
	Brees has thrown for 6,537 yards and 55 touchdowns in less than  
two full seasons as a starter. 
</P>
<P>
	Paterno has 314 victories and is tied with Amos Alonzo Stagg for  
third among the winningest coaches in major college history. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
