<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-22 19:00:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Joopy Doopy Wins Sunny Slopes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Joopy Doopy overtook Orangeman and Here's  
Zealous in the late going to win Friday's $78,350 Sunny Slopes 
Stakes in Santa Anita's Oak Tree meeting by a half-length. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Victor Espinoza, Joopy Doopy covered six furlongs in  
1:08 4-5 and paid $17.80, $6.60 and $3.40. The winning time was 2-5 
of a second off the stakes record set by Thisnearlywasmine in 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	The victory was the second in five lifetime starts for Joopy  
Doopy and was worth $47,010, increasing the career earnings of the 
2-year-old son of Gilded Time to $101,459. 
</P>
<P>
	Orangeman, the 2-1 second choice ridden by Chris McCarron,  
crossed the finish line a head in front of Here's Zealous and 
returned $4.20 and $2.40. 
</P>
<P>
	Here's Zealous, the 7-5 favorite ridden by Iggy Puglisi, was two  
lengths ahead of Magical Dragon at the wire and paid $2.20 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Valiant Vision was fifth and Cameron Pass last in the 24th  
running of the race for 2-year-olds. Each of the six entries 
carried 115 pounds except Cameron Pass, who carried 117. 
</P>
<P>
	There was an oddity in the eighth and final race of the day.  
West Of The Pecos and Lake William finished in a dead heat for 
first place, and Brigade and Maxaplenty tied for fourth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
