<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Toxic-School Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The Associated Press erroneously reported  
Oct. 21 that the Los Angeles school system plans to finish building 
a multimillion-dollar high school on a toxic site. 
</P>
<P>
	An independent panel recommended Oct. 20 that the project be  
completed but the school system has not yet made a final decision. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
