<HEADLINE> Ali's Daughter To Fight in W.Va. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHARLESTON, W.Va. (AP) -- Muhammad Ali's daughter is scheduled to  
fight her second professional match at Mountaineer Race Track and 
Gaming Resort in Chester Nov. 10. 
</P>
<P>
	Laila Ali's opponent has yet to be determined for the four-round  
bout. 
</P>
<P>
	Ali won her first professional fight Oct. 8 at Verona, N.Y., as  
her father watched. 
</P>
<P>
	Ali, who runs a nail salon in Los Angeles, decided a year ago  
she wanted to box professionally after trying the sport as a form 
of exercise. 
</P>
<P>
	The seven-fight card also includes a 10-round lightweight bout  
between Mike Griffith (21-6) of Cleveland and John Bailey (16-3-1) 
of New Cumberland. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
