<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Houston's Barkley To Retire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- Houston Rockets forward Charles Barkley said  
Friday he will announce his retirement Sunday, effective at 
season's end. 
</P>
<P>
	The 36-year-old Barkley has threatened several times in recent  
years to retire, but the 6-foot-6 forward insisted this time he 
means it. He said he will make the announcement at halftime of 
Sunday's exhibition game between the Rockets and Detroit Pistons at 
Birmingham, Ala. 
</P>
<P>
	Birmingham is less than a half-hour's drive from his hometown of  
Leeds, Ala., so his family will be on hand. 
</P>
<P>
	This will be Barkley's 16th NBA season.  
</P>
<P>
	``It's just time,'' said Barkley, who has been upgraded to  
questionable for Sunday's game after missing the last four 
preseason games with tendinitis in his right elbow. ``It's time. 
That's it. I'm not going to answer any more questions about it. 
It's just time. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't know what I'm going to do (after he retires). I might  
just take some time off. But I'm making it official Sunday. I'm 
announcing it there (in Birmingham) because that's my hometown, and 
I'll have a lot of family and friends there. This is my last year, 
period. I don't care how well I'm playing -- this is it. I want to 
get it over with, and that's it. I'm looking forward to it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Barkley has long been one of the league's top draws, especially  
internationally. He was on the original Dream Team, playing with 
Michael Jordan, Larry Bird and Magic Johnson on the juggernaut that 
won the gold medal at the 1992 Olympics in Barcelona. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1996, Barkley, then with the Phoenix Suns, teamed with  
current Rockets teammate Hakeem Olajuwon on the U.S. team that won 
a gold medal in Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
	``If Charles has decided that this is his last season, then we  
should all relish one more chance to be entertained by one of the 
most spectacular players in NBA history,'' NBA deputy commissioner 
Russ Granik told the Houston Chronicle. ``Charles is certainly a 
one-of-a-kind personality, but first and foremost, he is a truly 
great talent on the court.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Rockets owner Leslie Alexander agreed.  
</P>
<P>
	``I think he's one of the greatest who ever played the game,''  
Alexander said. ``He is a great player, but he also made the game 
fun. People love to be around Charles, and an attitude like that is 
rare in any sport. His routine will be missed.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Barkley averaged less than 10 rebounds only once, when he  
averaged 8.6 as a rookie with the Philadelphia 76ers in 1984-85. 
Entering this season, Barkley has scored 23,468 points (13th on the 
career list) and pulled down 12,337 rebounds, once leading the 
league (14.6 in 1986-87) and hauling in a career-high 33 in his 
first game as a Rocket. 
</P>
<P>
	He was the NBA's second leading rebounder last season with 12.3  
per game. 
</P>
<P>
	Alexander, who said he is not surprised by the decision, is  
happy to have Barkley play his last game as a Rocket. 
</P>
<P>
	``Definitely,'' Alexander said. ``It's nice to have a great one  
retire in your uniform. And he's one of the greatest of all.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
