<HEADLINE> Breeders Eliminations No Surprise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CAMPBELLVILLE, Ontario (AP) -- The Firepan, who won the Metro  
Pace last month at Woodbine, stamped himself the favorite for the 
$823,347 Breeders Crown 2-year-old colt pace with a strong 
performance Friday night in the elimination heats at Mohawk 
Racetrack. 
</P>
<P>
	Favorites dominated the night of elimination heats as the  
continent's best 2-year-old pacers and trotters tuned up for next 
Friday's $5.3 million Breeders Crown. 
</P>
<P>
	The Firepan, driven by John Campbell, battled I Scoot Hanover  
and Wicked Island before pulling away to win by 1 1/4 lengths in 
1:55.1. 
</P>
<P>
	Tyberwood finished second and I Scoot Hanover held on for third.  
</P>
<P>
	The Firepan will face, among others, Astreos, who won his  
elimination in 1:56.4 as the odds-on choice in front of driver 
Chris Christoforou. It was the fifth win in seven starts for 
Astreos. 
</P>
<P>
	Kirk Diggler, the 3-1 second choice driven by Ron Pierce, won  
the third elimination in 1:56.4. Favorite Twin B Champ was second 
by a nose. 
</P>
<P>
	The $662,529 2-year-old colt trot final appears to be wide open  
after impressive elimination performances by Dreamaster, Super 
Spicy and longshot Earl of Stormont. 
</P>
<P>
	Dreamaster, driven by Dave Magee, coasted home by five lengths  
over Monte Hall and Thunderous in 2:00.3. It was the seventh win in 
10 starts for the son of Victory Dream. 
</P>
<P>
	Super Spicy, a son of Super Bowl, won the fastest of the three  
trotting colt eliminations, a three-length winner over even-money 
favorite Credit Winner in 1:59.3. Driven by Dave Miller, Super 
Spicy won for the ninth time in 14 starts. 
</P>
<P>
	The third elimination went to 38-1 shot Earl of Stormont, driven  
by Trevor Ritchie, who split the pack in mid-stretch and posted a 
two-length win over Smokn Lantern and Berndt Hanover in 2:00.2. It 
was the fifth win in 10 starts for Earl of Stormont. 
</P>
<P>
	Eternal Camnation, the 2-year-old pacing filly sensation who  
went off as the 1-5 favorite with Eric Ledford in the sulky, staked 
her claim as the one to beat in the $637,833 final after jogging 
home 7 1/4 lengths ahead of CR Hot Salsa and Michelles Revenge in 
1:54.3. 
</P>
<P>
	The daughter of Cam Fella has won 11 of 12 starts and more than  
$340,000. 
</P>
<P>
	Her next test will likely come from undefeated Arts Virtue, who  
registered a two-length win over Armbro Terrace in 1:55.2 in her 
heat. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the fourth win for Arts Virtue, who just started racing  
Sept. 29 but has recorded several impressive victories, including a 
three-length win in the $394,100 Three Diamonds at Garden State 
Park on Oct. 15. 
</P>
<P>
	Unbeaten Cherished Victory stamped herself the likely choice for  
the $652,092 2-year-old filly trot final following a workmanlike 
half-length victory over long shot Echo Hanover, with Aviano two 
lengths back in third. 
</P>
<P>
	Her biggest challenge may come from Bold Dreamer, who recorded  
an impressive victory of 1:59.2 in her heat. 
  	   	
</P>
